data.meta_description:
101 likes, 0 comments - usapresidential on January 17, 2024: "On this day in 1893, Rutherford B. Hayes died from complications of a heart attack in Freemont, Ohio. He was 70 years old.⠀

After his wife's death in 1889, President Hayes felt like his soul had left with her. She was the love of his life. Some say his heart broke and never recovered. President Hayes passed away in the comforts of his own home, surrounded by his family. His last words were, "I know that I'm going where Lucy is."

His procession was led by Ohio Governor William McKinley, and Pres. Elect Grover Cleveland to his interment at Oakwood Cemetery
----
